speech.p:
asked the Minister of Labour (1) whether he is aware of the shortage in Leicester of labourers for the building of houses and the development of sites for houses, and that experienced building operatives are being sent out of the city to work in other districts; and whether he will take steps to prevent any continuance of this and to arrange for supplementing the labour

force so that there will be available for Leicester an adequate supply of manpower in this regard;

(2) whether he is aware that bricklayers and plasterers in Leicester are being compelled to do their own labouring in consequence of the serious shortage of assistance; and what steps he intends to take to alleviate this situation.
